    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/dr-cpb-hemolysis-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-review-board",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels for Model Risk Level 2. The six not-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out under MRL 2 requirements. The CFD model of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump is judged credible for the purpose of identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions in support of Class II CPB device submission. The assessment is submitted under ProfileMinimal; the intended-use scope is described in the bound requirement (https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2-req-001) and the supporting claim (https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-hemolysis-cfd-claim-001).",
